Material Information Summary – Exploration Results (Ios Gold Project)

Key Highlights

  • High-grade gold intercepts from historical drilling at Ios Gold Project (adjacent to Bridge Creek):
  • FG08: 5m @ 35.65g/t Au (incl. 1m @ 146g/t Au)
  • MPQC021: 3m @ 8.98g/t Au (incl. 1m @ 23.70g/t Au)
  • IOS018: 3m @ 8.00g/t Au (incl. 1m @ 16.40g/t Au)
  • MPQC031: 4m @ 7.54g/t Au (incl. 1m @ 27.00g/t Au)

  • MPQD047: 2m @ 12.67g/t Au (incl. 1m @ 21.00g/t Au)

  • Location: Ios is 3.5km north of Bridge Creek Gold Deposit on the Howley Anticline, a 30km gold-rich fold.

  • Mineralisation: Pod-like, quartz-sulphide veins within Zamu Dolerite, structurally controlled.
  • Next Steps: Planned drilling at Bridge Creek Project (27 RC holes) to extend known mineralization; Ios flagged as a high-priority follow-up target.

Resource Context (from Table 3)

  • Bridge Creek JORC Resource: 1.97Mt @ 1.12g/t Au (70.56koz, Inferred).
  • Empire Stockworks (QLD): 0.54Mt @ 0.97g/t Au (16.89koz, Indicated).

Material Information Summary (Exploration Results Announcement)

Key Highlights:

  • High-grade gold assays from rock chip/grab samples at Mt Secret prospect:
  • 153.5g/t Au (selective sample, not representative of bulk mineralization).
  • Soil sampling results confirm gold anomalies:
  • Mannix prospect: Up to 926ppb Au (600m x 600m anomaly).
  • Mt Secret prospect: Up to 282ppb Au (200m strike anomaly).
  • IP survey commenced at Mt Secret and Mannix to refine drill targets (results expected late July).
  • LiDAR interpretation identified 428 undocumented historical mine workings (40 adits, 40 shafts, 348 pits).
  • Maiden drilling program planned for Q3 2025, pending IP results and permitting.
  • Rockvale Project (Achill target): Soil sampling and mapping planned pending land access agreements.

Next Steps:

  • IP survey completion (mid-July) → drill target delineation.
  • Drill permit applications (late July).
  • Verification of LiDAR-identified historical workings (July onward).

Valuation Impact:

  • Confirms high-grade gold potential at Mt Secret/Mannix (IRGS analogies to Fort Knox/Kidston).
  • Exploration momentum supports near-term catalyst (drilling).

No material capital markets actions (e.g., raising, halt) identified.

Note: Selective samples (rock chips) are not representative of bulk grades. Forward-looking statements involve inherent risks.

Material Information Summary – Dart Mining NL (ASX: DTM) – Exploration Update

Key Highlights:

  • Drilling Results:
  • TRDD001A: 10.5m @ 2.63 g/t Au + 12.21 g/t Ag + 1.94% Zn (from 68.6m), including 3.1m @ 7.42 g/t Au + 25.42 g/t Ag + 6.37% Zn.
  • TRDD003: 1.9m @ 4.36 g/t Au + 6.13 g/t Ag (from 146.5m), including 0.4m @ 18.5 g/t Au + 25.6 g/t Ag.

  • TRDD009: 6.0m @ 1.57 g/t Au (from 116.0m), including 0.4m @ 17.7 g/t Au + 44.9 g/t Ag.

  • New Mineralised Zones:

  • 9 new lodes identified in 8 of 10 assayed drill holes, indicating wider stacked mineralisation at New Constitution and South Constitution.

  • High-grade intersections (e.g., 22.8 g/t Au over 0.3m in TRDD003) and significant zinc/silver credits.

  • Resource Growth Potential:

  • Confirmation of strike length akin to existing 150koz Inferred Resource (March 2025).

  • Potential for resource upgrade to include Indicated classification and open-pit development scenarios.

  • Next Steps:

  • Exploration Target statement to be completed in coming months.
  • Further drilling to test depth extensions (up to 450m) and regional targets.

Market Impact:

  • Results support resource expansion and potential economic studies (open pit viability highlighted).
  • High-grade intercepts may improve project economics (e.g., lower strip ratios for bulk mining).

No material financial or capital structure updates disclosed.
